rComments: Professor Sanner is one of the best Professors I've had at the University of Toronto. He is incredibly knowledgable and designs course content around relevant applications of knowledge. It is evident that he cares very much about the student's learning experience. He also has interesting lectures with plenty of fun anecdotes!

He is very strict, talent and knowledgeable. His lecture is in a non-standard, colloquial English, I think that's a pleasure for the native students, but hard for me as an international student to catch up with.

This professor has no idea how to teach despite his intelligence. Finals and midterms are solely based off of random "fun facts" he tells you in class about course material; essentially hypothetical scenarios that no one cares about. He doesn't account for different academic backgrounds among students and fails at evaluating students fairly.

rComments: Excellent prof! very up to date with current machine learning/data science research and passionate about passing the knowledge on to students Material is somewhat difficult, lectures are crucial to do well on exams, some coding experience would be helpful After 5 years of engineering courses at U of T, Scott is legitimately the best prof I've had

- Explains concepts very well, cares about students, good sense of humour - Relates things in a way that students can understand - Lots of homework though, if you're not up to speed on coding be prepared to do A LOT of extra work outside of class

Great teacher, interesting material, lots of work.
